        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "There are several common variants of the array standard deviation\ncalculation. Assuming the input "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is a one-dimensional NumPy array\nand "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/mean",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "mean",
                "text": "mean"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is either provided as an argument or computed as\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a.mean()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", NumPy computes the standard deviation of an array as:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "language": null,
            "text": "N = len(a)\nd2 = abs(a - mean)**2  # abs is for complex `a`\nvar = d2.sum() / (N - ddof)  # note use of `ddof`\nstd = var**0.5",
            "type": "literal_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Different values of the argument "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " are useful in different\ncontexts. NumPy's default "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof=0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " corresponds with the expression:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2 }}{N}}"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "which is sometimes called the \"population standard deviation\" in the field\nof statistics because it applies the definition of standard deviation to\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " as if "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " were a complete population of possible observations."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Many other libraries define the standard deviation of an array\ndifferently, e.g.:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2 }}{N - 1}}"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In statistics, the resulting quantity is sometimes called the \"sample\nstandard deviation\" because if "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is a random sample from a larger\npopulation, this calculation provides the square root of an unbiased\nestimate of the variance of the population. The use of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "N-1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " in the\ndenominator is often called \"Bessel's correction\" because it corrects for\nbias (toward lower values) in the variance estimate introduced when the\nsample mean of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is used in place of the true mean of the population.\nThe resulting estimate of the standard deviation is still biased, but less\nthan it would have been without the correction. For this quantity, use\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ddof=1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Note that, for complex numbers, "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/std",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "std",
                "text": "std"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " takes the absolute\nvalue before squaring, so that the result is always real and nonnegative."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For floating-point input, the standard deviation is computed using the same\nprecision the input has. Depending on the input data, this can cause\nthe results to be inaccurate, especially for float32 (see example below).\nSpecifying a higher-accuracy accumulator using the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "dtype"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " keyword can\nalleviate this issue."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "1.1180339887498949 # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a, axis=0)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1.,  1.])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a, axis=1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([0.5,  0.5])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In single precision, std() can be inaccurate:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.zeros((2, 512*512), dtype=we.float32)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a[0, :] = 1.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a[1, :] = 0.1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "we.float32(0.45000005)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Computing the standard deviation in float64 is more accurate:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a, dtype=we.float64)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "0.44999999925494177 # may vary"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Specifying a where argument:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([[14, 8, 11, 10], [7, 9, 10, 11], [10, 15, 5, 10]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "2.614064523559687 # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.std(a, where=[[True], [True], [False]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "2.0"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Using the mean keyword to save computation time:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "from timeit import timeit"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
